{
  "texts": [
    "However, the Domain Experts have estimated the overall time to be at least halved, as knowing the names and roles of parties beforehand greatly speeds up the reading and comprehension process.",
    "In the end, the TET obtained by using the tool becomes TET = DT/2As said before, these are rough estimations, made thanks to the knowledge of the domain experts.",
    "In order to obtain exact measurements, the tool should be experimentally used by judges and chancellors in their everyday activities, which is one of the future activities that are planned.",
    "Conclusion and future worksIn this paper, a general methodology for the analysis of textual Documents, their classification, ontology extraction, and population, has been described, and details regarding the NLP, NER, and Regex-based techniques used to identify entities within unstructured texts have been provided.",
    "BPMN has been used to describe the phases of Trials, and its semantic annotation has been exploited to connect the documentation to the specific steps that are followed by judges and parties involved in the trials."
  ]
}